<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>have a ball • have balls</xh5><p> <i>have a ball</i>—(coll.) have a good time; enjoy oneself: They had tea in the Japanese Garden, and then drove out to the beach. She was <u>having a ball</u>.</p><p> <i>have balls</i>—(coarse sl.) have great courage or audacity: It’s for sure that Martin <u>has balls</u> to cut class again, after we were caught yesterday.</p> </entry>
